column2:
Certain official/employees of this office were the subject of anonymous text-complaint alleging impropriety in the performance of duties. Specifically, text-complaint reaching the Central Office alleged that:

1. Gerry G. Jucar, Engineer IV, Construction Division, in the processing and review of Variation Order, is demanding cash value in return;

2. Alberto B. Esquejo, Jr., Engineer IV, Planning and Design Division, is personally preparing the As Staked Plan of various projects and demanding cash value in return;

3. Tomas A. Calasag, Engineer V, David L. Fernandez, Engineer IV, Arturo F. Prepose, Engineer III, and Emily Joy S. Buenavista, Engineer III, all of Quality Assurance and Hydrology Division, demand 1% testing fee from contractors without issuing receipt and refuse to sign documents unless cash is given.

